-- Soitec Plunges Most in Nine Months on Loss Forecast: Paris Mover
-- B y   V i d y a   R o o t
-- 2012-07-17T07:13:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/soitec-plunges-most-in-nine-months-on-loss-forecast-paris-mover.html
Soitec (SOI) , the French semiconductor
materials maker, tumbled the most in almost nine months in
Paris, after saying it expects an operating loss for the first
half.  The  shares fell  as much as 18 percent, the biggest intraday
drop since Oct. 18,  and were 42 cents lower at 2.30 euros as of
9:10 a.m.  After the close of trading yesterday, Soitec said its
first-quarter sales were down 27 percent to 60.3 million euros,
and that the company expects to post an  operating loss  of about
60 million euros in its fiscal half year ending September.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net  